## 3. Design tokens — CoinDCX (use ONLY these)

**Font:** Inter. **Weights:** 400, 500, 600.

### 3.1 Colors (light / dark)

Use only these semantic tokens (resolve via `context.colors.*` in Flutter).

**Light:** generalForegroundPrimary #000000E5, generalForegroundSecondary #0000008A, generalForegroundTertiary #00000054; generalBackgroundBgL0Web #F5F5F5, generalBackgroundBgL1 #FFFFFF, generalBackgroundBgL2 #F5F5F5, generalBackgroundBgL3 #F2F2F2; generalStrokeL1 #0000000A, generalStrokeL2 #00000014, generalStrokeL3 #00000038; actionForegroundPrimary #FFFFFF, actionBackgroundPrimary #4965D2, actionBackgroundSecondary #EDF0FB; positiveBackgroundPrimary #37B271, positiveBackgroundSecondary #EBF7F1; negativeBackgroundPrimary #E13B4D, negativeBackgroundSecondary #FCEBED; alertBackgroundPrimary #F7931A, alertBackgroundSecondary #FEF4E8.

**Dark:** generalForegroundPrimary #FFFFFFE5, generalForegroundSecondary #FFFFFF8A, generalForegroundTertiary #FFFFFF54; generalBackgroundBgL0Web #0A0A0A, generalBackgroundBgL1 #000000, generalBackgroundBgL2 #141414, generalBackgroundBgL3 #1F1F1F; generalStrokeL1 #FFFFFF14, generalStrokeL2 #FFFFFF1F, generalStrokeL3 #FFFFFF33; actionBackgroundPrimary #425BBD, actionBackgroundSecondary #292929; positiveBackgroundPrimary #37B271, positiveBackgroundSecondary #1C5939; negativeBackgroundPrimary #B42F3E, negativeBackgroundSecondary #441217; alertBackgroundPrimary #F7931A, alertBackgroundSecondary #4A2C08.

### 3.2 Sizes and radius (px)

**Spacing:** sizeGeneralXXXS=2, XXS=4, XS=8, S=12, M=16, L=20, XL=24, XXL=28, XXXL=32; sizePagePageMargin=20, sizePagePageMarginAlt=12. **Components:** sizeButtonButton=12, sizeButtonSButton=8; sizeChipChip=8; sizeInputInputH=16, sizeInputInputV=6. **Radius:** cornerRadiusGeneralXS=8, S=12, M=16, L=20; cornerRadiusCardCard=16, cornerRadiusCardSCard=8; cornerRadiusButtonButton=8; cornerRadiusInputInput=8; cornerRadiusBottomSheetBottomSheet=20.

### 3.3 Typography (style names only)

**UI:** uiText 14/20. **Body:** body 12/16, sBody 11/16, xsBody 9/12. **Label:** label 10/16, sLabel 8/12, xsLabel 7/12. **Headlines:** headline 16/20, lHeadline 20/24, xlHeadline 24/28. **Hero:** heroText 40/48, sHeroText 32/40. **Marketing:** marketingHeading 28/44, marketingSHeading 20/28, marketingBody 16/24, marketingNum 24/32. Use style names in code (e.g. **bodyR**, **labelSB**, **headlineM**); SB=600, M=500, R=400. Font family **Inter** only.

### 3.4 Typography selection guide — which style for which UI element

**GOLDEN RULE: When in doubt, use `uiTextR` (14/20). Never use anything below `bodyR` (12/16) for readable text. Styles at 10px and below (`label`, `sLabel`, `xsLabel`) are reserved for tags, badges, bottom-nav labels, and tiny count indicators only.**

| UI element | Style | Size | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| Page / screen title | `lHeadlineSB` or `xlHeadlineSB` | 20–24 | Top-level page heading |
| Section heading / AppBar title | `headlineSB` | 16 | Card or section title |
| Card hero value (price, total) | `lHeadlineSB` | 20 | Main financial figure on a card |
| Card secondary value (invested, P&L) | `uiTextSB` | 14 | Supporting numbers |
| Primary content / list-item title | `uiTextSB` or `uiTextM` | 14 | Most prominent text in a row |
| Body text / descriptions | `uiTextR` | 14 | **Default readable style** |
| Secondary info / subtitle / timestamp | `bodyR` or `bodyM` | 12 | Subordinate details |
| Caption / label above input field | `bodyR` | 12 | Floating or static field label |
| Input field value / placeholder | `uiTextR` | 14 | Text the user types or sees |
| Button text (primary, full-width) | `uiTextSB` | 14 | Standard buttons |
| Button text (small / compact) | `bodySB` | 12 | Inline or secondary buttons |
| Dropdown menu item | `uiTextR` | 14 | Each row in a dropdown |
| Tab label (L1 / L2) | `headlineSB` active / `headlineR` inactive | 16 | Page-level or section tabs |
| Tab label (L3 chip-style) | `bodySB` active / `bodyR` inactive | 12 | Pill/chip tabs |
| Toast message | `uiTextM` | 14 | Notification bar text |
| Error text below input | `bodyR` | 12 | Validation message |
| Bottom-nav label | `labelM` | 10 | Only here is 10px acceptable |
| Tag / badge / chip text | `sLabelSB` uppercase | 8 | Small colored pills |
| Tiny count indicator | `labelM` | 10 | E.g. notification count badge |

**Common mistakes to avoid:**
- Using `bodyR` (12px) for primary content — use `uiTextR` (14px) instead.
- Using `labelSB` (10px) for button text — use `uiTextSB` (14px) instead.
- Using `labelR` (10px) for captions above fields — use `bodyR` (12px) instead.
- Using `bodySB` (12px) for card values like amounts — use `uiTextSB` (14px) instead.
- Using `sBody` (11px) or `xsBody` (9px) for anything the user needs to read at a glance.

