## 5. Stack conventions

**General:** English; explicit types; PascalCase classes; camelCase members; snake_case files/dirs. **Riverpod only** for DI (no getIt). **Navigation:** native Flutter only (no go_router, auto_route, fluro). **Localisation:** intl + ARB/gen-l10n. **Code generation:** only for **intl** and **Isar**; **not** for Riverpod, Freezed, or testing.

### 5.1 Riverpod (manual providers only)

- **`ProviderScope`** at root. Define **`Provider`**, **`NotifierProvider`**, **`AsyncNotifierProvider`** by hand — **no** `@riverpod` / **riverpod_generator**.
- **Notifier** / **AsyncNotifier**; **immutable** state with hand-written classes (final fields, optional copyWith or Equatable) — **no Freezed**.
- **Controller pattern:** notifier methods update state; widgets **`ref.read(…notifier).executeLoad()`**. **`ref.watch`** in build; **`ref.read`** in callbacks.
- **Testing:** **mocktail** for mocks; **`ProviderScope(overrides: …)`** and **`ProviderContainer`** for notifier tests.

### 5.2 Navigation — native Flutter only

- **Do not** use **go_router**, **auto_route**, **fluro**, or any third-party navigation package.
- Use **`Navigator.push`** / **`Navigator.pop`** with **`MaterialPageRoute`** / **`CupertinoPageRoute`**, or Navigator 2.0 (**`Router`**, **`RouterDelegate`**, **`RouteInformationParser`**, **`BackButtonDispatcher`**) from **material.dart** / **cupertino.dart** / **widgets.dart**. Extras via constructor args or **`ModalRoute.of(context)?.settings.arguments`**.

### 5.3 DI, persistence, Crashlytics

- **DI:** Providers for **CrashReportingService**, **SecureStorageRepository**, **PreferencesRepository**, **Isar**; **`ref.read`** for one-shot deps. No **@Riverpod** annotations.
- **Isar:** Repository in domain; **Isar entity/code generation allowed** (build_runner + isar_generator). Indices and migrations on schema change.
- **shared_preferences:** Non-sensitive only; **PreferencesRepository** + **PreferencesKeys**.
- **flutter_secure_storage:** Tokens/secrets only; **SecureStorageRepository** behind Provider; never log.
- **Crashlytics:** Single **CrashReportingService** Provider; **FlutterError.onError** + **runZonedGuarded** in main; recordFatal / recordNonFatal; no PII in keys. **kDebugMode:** no-op or debug-only.

### 5.4 Clean architecture and folders

- **presentation** → **domain** ← **data**; domain has no Flutter imports.
- **Layout:** **lib/app/** (MaterialApp, ProviderScope, routing); **lib/core/** (theme, crash, providers, constants, extensions); **lib/features/<feature>/{data,domain,presentation}/**; **lib/shared/** (widgets, providers). Repositories + use cases + notifiers with hand-written immutable state.

### 5.5 Localisation — intl

- **intl** + Flutter **gen-l10n** (ARB → generated Dart). **Codegen for localisation is allowed.** Use generated **`AppLocalizations`** in UI; **never** raw user-facing strings. **DateFormat**, **NumberFormat**, **Intl.message** / ICU for plurals and placeholders.

### 5.6 Code generation — only intl and Isar

- **Allowed:** **intl** / gen-l10n (ARB → AppLocalizations), **Isar** (entity/schema via isar_generator).
- **Not allowed:** Riverpod annotations/generator, Freezed, json_serializable (unless team agrees), codegen for testing. Hand-write providers, state classes, and use **mocktail** without generated mocks.

### 5.7 Testing — mocktail

- **All** tests that need doubles use **mocktail** (Mock, registerFallbackValue, when, verify). Use **ProviderScope(overrides: …)** to inject mocks. Prefer **fake** where possible; **mock** where verification/stubbing is needed.

### 5.8 Performance

- **const** widgets; **ref.watch(provider.select(…))** for granular rebuilds; **ListView.builder** / slivers; **Image** cacheWidth/cacheHeight; **compute** / **Isolate.run** for heavy CPU; **RepaintBoundary** for expensive subtrees; no async/I/O in build.

